We created a boosting plugin to boost results from certain pages, this works flawlessly. Now our business is requesting to downrank results of type attachment. How can we identify if a result is of type attachment? I haven't found any useful info about this online. The org.apache.lucene.document.Document object only has fields, but what indexed field is the identifier for an attachment type?
Currently the code is like this:

{code:java}
@Override
public float boost(IndexReader reader, int doc, float score)
throws IOException
{
	Document document = reader.document(doc);
	IndexableField field = document.getField(SpaceKeyField);
	if (field != null) {
		String spaceKey = field.stringValue();
		if (document.getType().equals("Attachment")) { score *= DOWNRANK_ATTACHMENT; }
		else if (spaceKeysToBoost.contains(spaceKey)) { score *= BOOST_COR_SPACE; }
	}
	return score;
}
{code}


*document.getType().equals("Attachment")* obviously doesnt work. But with what working if-statement does this work?
Thanks in advance!

